    <note>Pei(1) Ruren [29637] The sequence of events suggests that Ruan(1) Chun [29635] was stationed in Huaian Fu, Hai Zhou when serving as a military leader in the Wako campaign. At this time, the marriage between his son, Jialin [29636] and Ruren was probably contracted. Their son, Ruan(1) Shixun [29640] with his younger brother, Shimei [25641] migrated to Huaian Fu, Shanyang Xian from Linjiang Fu, Qingjiang Xian in order to avoid the military registers at the end of the Ming, i.e. moved to a county locate near the home of their mother. Ruan Yuan, WJ, erji, 2.368.</note>
